                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="19765" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 20 Sep 2006 09:16:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out! It&apos;s a bit of a pain that databases differ in such subtle details. As you noticed, we also changed our strategy in Spring 1.2 there, since it was found to be the most compatible strategy for all databases that we tested against.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To be able to properly adapt to Informix, our StatementCreatorUtils uses &quot;PreparedStatement.setObject(index, null)&quot; for null values with unknown SQL type on Informix now. We simply have a special check that detects Informix via the metadata&apos;s database product name, choosing the appropriate null strategy accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
